    "script": "In the dead of night, a violent storm battered the disciples' boat on the Sea of Galilee. Suddenly, Jesus appeared, walking on water. Peter stepped out to meet him but faltered when he saw the waves. As he sank, Jesus saved him, calming the storm. The disciples worshipped, proclaiming him the Son of God.",
    "tone": "dramatic",
    "shots": [
      "A small wooden boat is violently tossed by towering waves under a pitch-black sky, with terrified disciples clinging to the sides as lightning illuminates the stormy Sea of Galilee at night.",
      "A figure in a flowing robe, Jesus, strides calmly across the churning water toward the boat, his silhouette glowing faintly against the dark storm clouds.",
      "Peter, dressed in simple first-century clothing, steps hesitantly out of the boat onto the raging waves, his face a mix of awe and fear as wind whips his hair.",
      "The aposle Peter's eyes widen in panic as he looks down at the frothing water swallowing his feet, his arms flailing as he begins to sink beneath the stormy surface.",
      "Jesus reaches out with a strong hand to grasp the apostle Peter's wrist, pulling him up from the waves as the wind suddenly stills around them, moonlight breaking through the clouds.",
      "The disciples kneel in the now-calm boat, their faces illuminated by soft moonlight as they raise their hands in worship toward Jesus, who stands serenely on the water."
